data.title: EXCLUSIVE: STAR SPOOKED OUT
data.meta_description: SPOOKS star Raza Jaffrey has been axed.
data.text:
SPOOKS star Raza Jaffrey has been axed.

Raza, 32, MI5's Zafar Younis, is expected to be killed off at the end of the fifth series of the BBC spy drama this year.

A source said: "It was decided the character couldn't be taken any further."

Raza, in Spooks since 2004, is the second star to go during the series - Nicola Walker, who plays Ruth Evershed, quit after becoming pregnant.

Last year the Mirror revealed Raza and Miranda Raison, 29, who plays Jo Portman, are lovers.
